description: A weathered dark wood cabinet sets against a thin cast iron railing that separates the octagonal patio from a field of wildflowers.  Set in the center of the riverstone-paved area is a polished wood workbench.  Along the railing, a strand of honeysuckle twirls and weaves and fills the area with a sweet aroma.  Attracted by the scent, several bees buzz back and forth along the blossoms of the colorful vine.

Attracted by the light, several moths flutter over the blossoms of the colorful vine.  Several lamps strung along the edge of the patio provide light for nocturnal activities.
